    "ideation": "The salt shaker animation is a study in gravity, inversion, and granular dispersal. The face acts as the shaker itself. It begins upright and neutral, then performs a deliberate 180-degree emotional inversion. The eyes move from a steady gaze to a downward, high-intensity squint to simulate the 'cap' side of the shaker being pointed at a meal. The mouth represents the flow of salt: starting as a solid, static line, it breaks into a high-frequency, jittery ripple during the 'shake' to mimic thousands of tiny grains falling. The color palette is clinical and crystalline—whites and pale silvers—to evoke the mineral nature of salt.",
